What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Infrared Vision Systems Market?

Infrared Vision Systems Market Analysis

The infrared vision systems market is witnessing advancements such as AI-driven thermal imaging, improving accuracy in various applications. The integration of infrared sensors in the automotive and defense sectors is growing due to enhanced safety features. Portable and wearable infrared devices are also gaining traction, driving market expansion. These technologies enable precise detection in low-visibility environments, fueling broader adoption and market growth.

Infrared Vision Systems Market Size

The global infrared vision systems market size was valued at USD 6.97 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 10.53 billion by 2031, with a CAGR of 5.3% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

Infrared Vision Systems Market Trends

“Increasing Use in Automotive Safety Systems”

A major trend driving growth in the infrared vision systems market is their increasing integration into automotive safety systems. As vehicle manufacturers strive to enhance driver assistance technologies, infrared vision systems have become crucial for features including night vision, pedestrian detection, and collision avoidance. For instance, companies such as BMW and Audi are incorporating advanced infrared cameras into their luxury vehicles, allowing for improved nighttime visibility and enhanced safety features. This trend reflects a growing demand for high-tech solutions in automotive safety, pushing the adoption of infrared vision systems across the industry.

